{
  "id": "broadside-5kfm.17",
  "title": "feed.rs: RSS link URL injected into HTML without escaping, bypasses sanitizer",
  "description": "src/feed.rs:55: the link URL from a feed entry is interpolated directly into an href attribute and link text: format\\!(r#\"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"{url}\\\"\u003e{url}\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\"#). If the URL contains a double-quote (e.g., https://example.com/?a=\\\"\u003e\u003cscript\u003e...) it breaks out of the href attribute. The assembled html string is appended AFTER sanitize::sanitize_html() was called on body_html, so this injected fragment is never sanitized. An attacker controlling a feed can inject arbitrary HTML into posts delivered to followers. Fix: HTML-escape the URL before interpolating it into the href attribute and text, or pass the final assembled html through sanitize_html() before storing.",
